I ALMOST FREAKIN DIED!

This morning i went to Dondero to teach swim lessons and after the first class 4 kids passed out in the locker room. Then all the instructors noticed that they too had head aches, were really dizzy, and felt like they were going to pass out. So everyone had to get out of the water,parents came to collect their kids and started drying off. In the mean while, on the pool deck 2 instructors passed out, so we knew we all had to like, get away from the pool. So we were all in the hall, passing out, and when 6+ people have passed out and no ones being contacted for help its kinda a really serious problem.
I called my dad, and he called 911. 5 firetrucks, 4 ambulances, a swat team, and 4 cop cars later the rumor was that the pool was contaminated with Carbon Monoxide a level of 500 units (meaning deadly).
All the instrucotrs were taken in ambulances to beaumont and were immediatly put on oxygen.


I felt sooooo sick, i was shaking, and my heart was racing. And my heart doesnt race. i had a pulse of 110.... which is absolutly crazy comparing to when i run, my pulse is only 76. Im not an out of shape person, my heart was like pounding and i couldnt breathe.... ahhhh

When your exposed to Carbon Monoxide they give you ratings 1-19 meaning you were expose, 20 being toxic = Something is wrong with you and its scarey, and 35 meaning your cashed out, dead. While i was at school i was at a 21 (the Dr. said that was my level prior to treatment)but after 2 1/2 hours on oxygen i was at a 14. which was good.

5 hours later on oxygen and a I.V (which hurt like a mother my i mention) Steve visited me. That was nice. Thanks Steve. <3

I still have the worst head ache of my life tho.

The good news is that i got 2 pairs of scrubs tho :^)

SOOOOOOOOOOOOOO kids, stay away from carbon monoxide, Kay?

Oh yeah, the school has to pay for all of our medical bills. HAHA.

Last spring break was fun. Steve held my hand in his DADS TAURUS. HOTTTT.
